}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2023-08-04T16:19:15Z","updated_at":"2023-08-04T16:21:16Z","body":"Yes. Confirmed to reproduce at https://github.com/rails/rails/commit/36597e2093add6457e213b3691746d1b27aaed07.\r\n\r\nI've also dug into it again, but #48871 doesn't seem to fix my use case. In the `test_with_entity` case, the `attribute` in `ActiveModel::Error.full_message` is `entity.base`. So now it's changed to `entity` and the key passed to `ActiveModel::Translation#human_attribute_name` is different than before.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/rails/rails/blob/36597e2093add6457e213b3691746d1b27aaed07/activemodel/lib/active_model/error.rb#L52\r\n\r\nBased on the requirements of #48408, the expected behavior is probably:\r\n\r\n- Return a translation if `entity.base` exists in locale data.\r\n- Returns \"Entity\" instead of \"Entity base\" if there is no translation\r\n\r\nExcluding the \"base\" string from the translation defaults seems to work as expected, but I haven't found a good way to do it.","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1665871767/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"wata727","id":9624059,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk2MjQwNTk=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/9624059?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727","html_url":"https://github.com/wata727","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1665889601","html_url":"https://github.com/rails/rails/issues/48884#issuecomment-1665889601","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/48884","id":1665889601,"node_id":"IC_kwDNIULOY0t1QQ","user":{"login":"rafaelfranca","id":47848,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODQ4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47848?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca","html_url":"https://github.com/rafaelfranca","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2023-08-04T16:32:31Z","updated_at":"2023-08-04T16:32:31Z","body":"Ok. I got it now. I don't think we can fix this. Either we remove `Base` from the error message, or we allow the `entity.base` attribute to exist. `base` ins't an attribute, so setting I18n to translate `base` doesn't make much sense.\r\n\r\nThe attribute you have in that test is called `comment.entity` which you renamed to be `Comment` that is why you get the message as `Comment This operation is not allowed`.\r\n\r\n[In non-nested errors, `base` errors just return the message and aren't even translated](https://github.com/rails/rails/blob/36597e2093add6457e213b3691746d1b27aaed07/activemodel/test/cases/error_test.rb#L174-L177). Probably that is what we should be doing here.\r\n\r\nThis will probably be another breaking change to someone since to be able to translate errors on base they will have to add the error already translated.","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1665889601/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"rafaelfranca","id":47848,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODQ4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47848?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca","html_url":"https://github.com/rafaelfranca","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1665901277","html_url":"https://github.com/rails/rails/issues/48884#issuecomment-1665901277","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/48884","id":1665901277,"node_id":"IC_kwDNIULOY0ui3Q","user":{"login":"rafaelfranca","id":47848,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODQ4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47848?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca","html_url":"https://github.com/rafaelfranca","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2023-08-04T16:43:53Z","updated_at":"2023-08-04T17:22:34Z","body":"~~This is worse than I thought. `message` on the `base` attribute is translatable, but `full_message` isn't ðŸ¤¦ðŸ½~~. I'm inclined to revert that change all together for 7.0 and really rethink how this should behave in 7.1.","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1665901277/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"rafaelfranca","id":47848,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODQ4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47848?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca","html_url":"https://github.com/rafaelfranca","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1665957766","html_url":"https://github.com/rails/rails/issues/48884#issuecomment-1665957766","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/48884","id":1665957766,"node_id":"IC_kwDNIULOY0x_hg","user":{"login":"wata727","id":9624059,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk2MjQwNTk=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/9624059?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727","html_url":"https://github.com/wata727","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2023-08-04T17:31:33Z","updated_at":"2023-08-04T17:31:33Z","body":"> so setting I18n to translate base doesn't make much sense.\r\n> [In non-nested errors, base errors just return the message and aren't even translated](https://github.com/rails/rails/blob/36597e2093add6457e213b3691746d1b27aaed07/activemodel/test/cases/error_test.rb#L174-L177). Probably that is what we should be doing here.\r\n\r\nAgreed.\r\n\r\nBut the next issue is that for my use case I want to translate without \"Comment\" whereas for #48408 use case they want to translate with \"Comment\". I'm not sure which one is right, but if you expect `base` to return messages as-is, the different behavior between autosave and otherwise can be tricky.\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\n# frozen_string_literal: true\r\n\r\nrequire \"bundler/inline\"\r\n\r\ngemfile(true) do\r\n  source \"https://rubygems.org\"\r\n\r\n  git_source(:github) { |repo| \"https://github.com/#{repo}.git\" }\r\n\r\n  # Activate the gem you are reporting the issue against.\r\n  gem \"activerecord\", '7.0.6'\r\n  gem \"sqlite3\"\r\nend\r\n\r\nrequire \"active_record\"\r\nrequire \"minitest/autorun\"\r\nrequire \"logger\"\r\n\r\n# This connection will do for database-independent bug reports.\r\nActiveRecord::Base.establish_connection(adapter: \"sqlite3\", database: \":memory:\")\r\n\r\nI18n.backend.store_translations(\r\n  :en,\r\n  activerecord: {\r\n    attributes: {\r\n      comment: {\r\n        entity: \"Comment\"\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n)\r\n\r\nActiveRecord::Schema.define do\r\n  create_table :comments, force: true do |t|\r\n  end\r\n\r\n  create_table :entities, force: true do |t|\r\n    t.integer :comment_id\r\n  end\r\nend\r\n\r\nclass Comment < ActiveRecord::Base\r\n  has_one :entity, autosave: true\r\n\r\n  validates :entity, presence: true\r\nend\r\n\r\nclass Entity < ActiveRecord::Base\r\n  validate ->() { errors.add(:base, \"is not allowed\") }\r\nend\r\n\r\nclass BugTest < Minitest::Test\r\n  def test_with_entity\r\n    comment = Comment.new\r\n    comment.build_entity\r\n\r\n    assert_predicate(comment, :invalid?)\r\n    assert_equal([\"Comment is not allowed\"], comment.errors.full_messages.map(&:strip))\r\n  end\r\n\r\n  def test_entity\r\n    entity = Entity.new\r\n\r\n    assert_predicate(entity, :invalid?)\r\n    assert_equal([\"Entity is not allowed\"], entity.errors.full_messages.map(&:strip))\r\n  end\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\n# Running:\r\n\r\n.F\r\n\r\nFinished in 0.010377s, 192.7376 runs/s, 385.4753 assertions/s.\r\n\r\n  1) Failure:\r\nBugTest#test_entity [test.rb:65]:\r\nExpected: [\"Entity is not allowed\"]\r\n  Actual: [\"is not allowed\"]\r\n\r\n2 runs, 4 assertions, 1 failures, 0 errors, 0 skips\r\n```\r\n\r\n> I'm inclined to revert that change all together for 7.0 and really rethink how this should behave in 7.1.\r\n\r\nThank you for your consideration. I'm happy if there is anything I can help.","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1665957766/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"wata727","id":9624059,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk2MjQwNTk=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/9624059?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727","html_url":"https://github.com/wata727","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wata727/repos","events_url":"https://api.g